description: Collects Transformers: Armada (2002) #1-5. Written by Chris Sarracini. Art by James Raiz, Rob Armstrong, and Edwin Garcia. Learn where the Mini-Cons came from, and why Optimus Prime and Megatron want them so badly! Starting out on Cybertron, this series moves quickly to Earth, where the battle between the Autobots and Decepticons rages on!
name: Volume 1: First Contact

description: Collects Transformers: Armada (2002) #6-11. Written by Chris Sarracini. Art by James Raiz, Rob Armstrong, and Edwin Garcia.
name: Volume 2: Fortress

description: Collects Transformers: Armada (2002) #12-18. Written by Simon Furman. Art by Guido Guidi, Don Figueroa, and Elaine To. Transformers Armada and G1 clash explosively in this ultimate Transformers saga. It is the beginning of the end as a chaotic force from beyond the Armada-verse starts to make its presence felt, dispatching five lethal heralds to soften up both the Autobots and the Decepticons. With Optimus Prime stranded on an alternate Cybertron, one about to be consumed, no happy endings are guaranteed!
name: Volume 3: Worlds Collide

description: Collects Transformers: Armada (2002) #1-5. Written by Chris Sarracini. Art and cover by James Raiz. Get ready for one of the wildest Transformers rides from the past! The DECEPTICONS, feeding off the energy of captured MINI-CONS, are about to begin a hostile takeover of the Transformers home planet, CYBERTRON. Do OPTIMUS PRIME and the heroic AUTOBOTS stand a chance of defending the planet? This long-requested tale is finally back in print!
name: IDW Edition - Volume 1

description: Collects Transformers: Armada (2002) #6-11. Written by Simon Furman. Art by Pat Lee and Guido Guidi. Simon Furman, Generation 1 artist supreme Pat Lee, and the talented Guido Guidi take the saga of Transformers: Armada to new heights! This second volume of Transformers: Armada has it all-a fortress base on the moon, a secret enclave of Mini-Cons, MEGATRON on the offensive, OPTIMUS PRIME on a collision course with disaster, the deadly debut of the Destruction Team, Rad in the firing line, and the power of the Star Saber!
name: IDW Edition - Volume 2

description: Collects Transformers: Armada (2002) #12-18. Written by Simon Furman. Art by Guido Guidi, Don Figueroa, and Elaine To. Transformers Armada and G1 clash explosively in this ultimate Transformers saga. It is the beginning of the end as a chaotic force from beyond the Armada-verse starts to make its presence felt, dispatching five lethal heralds to soften up both the Autobots and the Decepticons. With Optimus Prime stranded on an alternate Cybertron, one about to be consumed, no happy endings are guaranteed!
name: IDW Edition - Volume 3

description: Carlos, Rad and the mini-con Swindle are attacked by Starscream, Cyclonus and Demolisher...but that's only the start of the destruction as Hot Shot, Red Alert, Smokescreen, Megatron and Optimus Prime enter the fray! Script by Brandon Easton, pencils by Don Figueroa, inks by Elaine To.
name: Free Comic Book Day Edition

description: Collects Transformers: Energon (2002-2004) #19-23. Written by Simon Furman. Art by Guido Guidi and Joe Ng. Cover by Guido Guidi. Ten years after Unicron attacked Cybertron, the planet is seemingly at peace, with most of the Decepticons absorbed into the community. However, Optimus Prime is still not happy, and fears another attack from Unicron. The High Council are skeptical of this. However, events soon lead OPTIMUS to realize that not only is Unicron still functioning... but is on his way to a rich seam of Energon on Earth!
name: Volume 1

description: Helen continues her advances towards Sam and Jerome warns him to keep his distance. Later, Sam walks in on Helen and Vivian. Helen makes Vivian leave so she and Sam can be alone. Meanwhile Dr. Crawford inspects the patients progress in Farmhouse and he's pleased with the results so far. Naomi has some news for Sam and it's not good. To get some perspective Sam has dinner over his old high school friend Mike's house. That night Sam has another dream about his mother.
